negotiator.session

Class Round

  • java.lang.Object
    • negotiator.session.Round

  • public class Round
extends java.lang.Object
    Represents a single round in a negotiation session. A round is a part of a negotiation where all participants can respond to the current state of the negotiation. A Round consists of Turn which may or may not have an Action. Rounds are contained in the Session object. A party can have multiple turns in a single round.
    Author:
    David Festen

      • getActions

        public java.util.List<Action> getActions()
        Gets the actions in done in this round. If a turn is not executed, it shouldn't have an action. This means that in practice, you can use this method if you want to know the executed actions of this turn, even while it is still busy.
        Returns:
        A list of all actions done this turn.

      • getMostRecentAction

        public Action getMostRecentAction()
        get the last item of the getActions() list, which in practice should be the most recent action of this round.
        Returns:
        The most recently executed action in this round. Null if no action has been executed yet.
